10.10 Floyd-Warshall (all-pairs shortest paths) 
def floyd_warshall(n, w): 
 dist = [row[:] for row in w] # copy 
 for k in range(n): 
 for i in range(n): 
 for j in range(n): 
 if dist[i][k] + dist[k][j] < dist[i][j]: 
 dist[i][j] = dist[i][k] + dist[k][j] 
 return dist 
Time: O(V³). Great when V is small (say, ≤ 400). 
